                        <interp inst="t18670819-name-168" type="given" value="JAMES WILLIAM"></interp>JAMES WILLIAM RIVERS.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a tobacconist, of 83, Fleet Street—on 10th July the prisoner came for half an ounce of tobacco, and gave me a florin—I gave him change and he left—I found it was bad, marked it, and put it in my pocket—he came again next day for half an ounce of tobacco, tendered another bad florin, and I gave him in charge with the two florins.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Had you any suspicion the first time that the money was bad? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, because I had seen you half a dozen times before, and you always paid with the same coin—I did not stop you, because my suspicion was not aroused till you had gone.</p>
